p:
LC–MS analysis of 1 yielded a molecular formula of C 22H 31NO 5, obtained by high-resolution electrospray ionization MS (HRESIMS) from the [M + H] + ion at m/ z 390.2270 (calcd for C 22H 32NO 5 +, m/ z 390.2275, Δ = 1.2 ppm) and from the [M + Na] + ion at m/ z 412.2089 (calcd for C 22H 31NO 5Na +, m/ z 412.2094, Δ = 1.3 ppm) ( Figures S2–S4). The [M + H] + ion showed strong source decay via sequential loss of H 2O and CH 2O, indicating a labile methoxy group attached to a nonaliphatic substructure ( Figure S4). The fragmentation pattern shows a stable substructure containing most of the heteroatoms (C 7H 7NO 4) and did not fit to any of the 28 compounds with the above sum formula currently listed in the Dictionary of Natural Products ( Figure S5, Schemes S1 and S2).
